http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Infosys-Foundation-to-construct-choultry-at-Kidwai-memorial-institute/article14015808.ece

Sudha Murty, chairperson of the Infosys Foundation, has agreed to construct a choultry at a cost of Rs. 50 crore on the premises of the Kidwai Memorial Institute of Oncology in Bengaluru to help relatives of cancer patients admitted to the institute and outpatients.Disclosing this to The Hindu on Friday, Minister of State for Medical Education Sharanprakash Patil said that Ms. Murty would also provide another Rs. 2 crore to take up the repair of the existing choultry at the institute.Dr. Patil said that Ms. Murty had also agreed to provide Rs. 6 crore for constructing another operation theatre complex there. To a question, he said that Ms. Murty had promised to provide funds for constructing a choultry at the cancer hospital in Kalaburagi too.He said that during his meeting with Ms. Murty in Bengaluru recently, he informed her about the urgent need for constructing a choultry in Kalaburagi. Ms. Murthy said that she would send a team of engineers to inspect the site where the choultry was proposed to be constructed.